Schaeuble Sees 80 Percent Majority for EFSF Law, Rundschau Says

-- B y   J a n a   R a n d o w
-- 
2011-09-21T06:41:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-21/schaeuble-sees-80-percent-majority-for-efsf-law-rundschau-says.html
German Finance Minister  Wolfgang Schaeuble  said lawmakers from opposition parties will help the
government pass changes to the European Financial Stability
Facility,  Frankfurter Rundschau  reported, citing an interview.  “With such a difficult question, it is only natural that
there are colleagues who have severe stomachaches” within the
ruling Christian Democratic bloc, Schaeuble told the newspaper.
“We have a majority of 80 percent for the law in the
Bundestag,”  Germany ’s lower house of parliament, when it goes
to a vote on Sept. 29.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jana Randow in Frankfurt at 
 jrandow@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Craig Stirling at   cstirling1@bloomberg.net  